Oatmeal Raisin Cookies
source|
url|
aliases|
tags|
activeTime|
totalTime|
yield|4 dozen cookies
description|

# ingredients
1|cup|margarine or softened butter
1|cup|firmly packed brown sugar
1/2|cup|granulated sugar
2||egg
1|tsp|vanilla extract
1 1/2|cup|all purpose flour
1|tsp|baking soda
1|tsp|cinnamon
1/2|tsp|salt
3|cup|oats
1|cup|raisins

# instructions
Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat margarine and sugars together until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins, mix well.
Drop by rounded TBSPs onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, remove to wire rack.
1 minute on cookie sheet, 5 minutes on rack

# notes
Bar cookies: Bake 30-35 minutes in 13 by 9 inch baking pan.
